  "prompt": "Is there any good institute for differently abled child near Noida areas?",
  "response": "Yes, there are several institutes and organizations near Noida that cater to the needs of differently-abled children. Here are a few you can consider:\n\n1. **The Miracle Foundation** - They provide support and services for children with disabilities by focusing on education, therapy, and empowerment.\n\n2. **Sankalp Special School** - Located in Noida, this institute specializes in providing education and therapy for children with various disabilities.\n\n3. **Asha Kiran School** - This is another special school in Noida that offers support for children with disabilities, emphasizing inclusive education and individual development plans.\n\n4. **Sankalp Rehabilitation Trust** - While primarily focused on rehabilitation for children with disabilities, they also offer educational opportunities and vocational training.\n\n5. **Enable India** - While based in Bangalore, they provide training and job placement for differently-abled individuals and can have programs or partnerships in other cities.\n\n6. **National Institute for the Empowerment of Persons with Multiple Disabilities (NIEPMD)** - Though located in Chennai, they provide resources and training programs that may be beneficial, with some outreach in other areas.\n\nIt's advisable to visit these institutions, if possible, to assess their programs, staff, and environment to find the best fit for your child. Additionally, checking online reviews and connecting with local parent groups can provide more insights.",
